.TH NEO-INIT 1 "March 2026" "neo 0.1.0" "Neo CLI Manual"
.SH NAME
neo-init \- initialize a .neo/ project directory and register the repo
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B neo init
.RB [ \-\-force ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B neo init
initializes a new neo project in the current directory. It performs the following:
.PP
.RS
.IP 1. 3
Creates the .neo/agents/ directory for project-local agent definitions.
.IP 2. 3
Detects the default branch of the repository (main, master, etc.).
.IP 3. 3
Registers the repository in the global neo configuration.
.IP 4. 3
Creates the global configuration file if it doesn't exist (with default budget settings).
.RE
.PP
After initialization, run
.B neo doctor
to verify the setup is complete.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-force
Re-register the repository even if .neo/agents/ already exists. Without this
flag, neo init will refuse to run if the project appears to be already initialized.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B .neo/agents/
Created directory for project-local custom agent definitions.
.TP
.B ~/.neo/config.yml
Global configuration file (created if missing).
.SH EXAMPLES
Initialize a new project:
.PP
.RS
.nf
cd /path/to/your/repo
neo init
.fi
.RE
.PP
Re-initialize an existing project:
.PP
.RS
.nf
neo init --force
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
.ne/agents/ already exists (use --force to override).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR neo (1),
.BR neo-doctor (1),
.BR neo-repos (1)
